SONAR
=====

The sonar command is an active sweep from a sonar-equipped ship: it
sweeps terrain like 'sradar' (a shorter-ranged formula, capped at 7
hexes), and separately pings nearby ships — including submarines,
which neither 'sradar' nor 'look' can ever find. If a pinged ship's
owner has the sonar flag on (see 'info toggle'), they get a telegram
telling them someone pinged them.

COMMAND
-------
  sonar SHIP-SPEC     Sweep from ship(s) matching SHIP-SPEC
  sonar *             Sweep from every eligible owned ship

SHIP-SPEC accepts a uid, a uid range, a comma list, "*", "~", or a
fleet letter.

It's also available inline, mid-route, as the 's' token in a
'navigate' command (ships only) — see 'info navigate'.

ELIGIBILITY
-----------
  The ship's type must have sonar capability (not every ship does —
  check 'show ship b' or the type's description). The ship must
  currently be sitting in a sea sector.

RANGE
-----
    range  = vrnge * (50 + tech) / (200 + tech)
    srange = min(7, 7 * range * effic / 200)

  Shorter and more tightly capped than 'sradar'/'radar' — sonar
  trades reach for the ability to find submerged subs at all.

WHAT YOU SEE
------------
  Terrain sweep: same display rules as 'radar' (actual mnemonic
  within range/3, '?' beyond, own/sea/mountain/wasteland always
  shown), rendered as a grid centered on your ship.

  Ship pings: any foreign ship within ping range shows as "Sonar
  detects Nation #N <shiptype> @ x,y" — except a HOSTILE-or-worse
  submarine, which is partly or fully obscured depending on how your
  ship's own visual range compares to the sub's stealth: sometimes
  you only get "Sonar detects sub #N", sometimes just the ship type
  with no nation, sometimes the full nation+type. A Friendly-or-
  better sub is always shown in full, same as any other ship.

  Ping range and terrain-sweep range are computed separately, so a
  ship can sometimes be pinged (and its owner notified) slightly
  outside the area actually rendered on your grid, or vice versa —
  matches the original mechanic exactly.

KNOWN GAPS (v1)
---------------
  4.4.1's sonar additionally requires an unobstructed all-water line
  of sight to each contact — land, or another ship, blocks the ping.
  Not modeled here; this is a plain radius sweep, same fidelity level
  as 'radar'/'sradar'/'lradar'. Mine detection at very high tech is
  also not ported — no mine-laying/sweeping mechanic exists in
  empire5 yet at all (see 'info bomb' for the same gap noted against
  the inline nav tokens).

EXAMPLES
--------
  sonar *          Sweep from every eligible owned ship.
  sonar 5          Sweep from ship 5 only.

